tch%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20lucky%20in%20that%20we%20were%20not%20overly%20aggressive%20previously.%20I%20think%20sometimes%2C%20especially%20with%20misinformation%20and%20other%20things%2C%20people%20moved%20the%20line.%20And%20we%20had%20always%20consistently%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BListen%2C%20you%20should%20be%20free%20to%20say%20what%20you%20want.%20It's%20how%20you%20say%20it.%20You%20can't%20be%20spewing%20hate.%20You%20can't%20be%20threatening%20violence%20%E2%80%A6%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20you%20could%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20take%20ivermectin%20to%20deal%20with%20my%20COVID.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorrect.%20We%20did%20have%20a%20policy%20%5Bto%20deal%20with%5D%20someone%20whose%20sole%20purpose%20is%20to%20spread%20misinformation%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20really%20happen%20on%20Twitch.%20We%20don't%20have%20the%20viral%20spreading%20of%20information.%20More%20often%20than%20not%2C%20what%20people%20say%20on%20Twitch%20is%20a%20manifestation%20of%20what%20they%20hear%20through%20the%20other%20platforms.%20So%20someone%20might%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I%20read%20a%20Facebook%20post%20the%20other%20day%20that%20said%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you've%20always%20been%20sort%20of%20looser%20than%20some%20of%20the%20other%20platforms.%20And%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-letter-jim-jordan-meta-facebook-censorship-politics-meaning-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Ethe%20Jim%20Jordans%20of%20the%20world%20are%20going%20after%20you%20and%20subpoenaing%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20and%20asking%20you%20to%20explain%20why%20you%20censored%20so-and-so.%20Is%20that%20because%20it's%20just%20a%20different%20platform%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20what%20Twitch%20is%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20because%20we%20have%20not%20been%20getting%20into%20that%20space.%20In%20general%2C%20we%20have%20not%20waded%20into%20censoring%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20talk%20about%20Twitter%20as%20a%20town%20square.%20Twitter's%20not%20really%20a%20town%20square%20because%20it%20just%20spreads%20all%20over%20the%20place.%20In%20a%20town%20square%2C%20you're%20either%20in%20the%20town%20square%20or%20you're%20not.%20And%20on%20a%20Twitch%20channel%2C%20either%20you're%20watching%20the%20channel%20live%20or%20you're%20not.%20If%20someone%20doesn't%20want%20to%20watch%20the%20channel%2C%20don't%20watch%20it.%20It%20doesn't%20algorithmically%20suddenly%20appear%20in%20their%20feed.%20You%20show%20up%3B%20you%20watch%20a%20channel.%20If%20you%20don't%20want%20someone%20watching%20your%20channel%2C%20you%20can%20ban%20them%20and%20stop%20them%20from%20watching%20your%20channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Live%20streamer%20Kai%20Cenat%20makes%20his%20entrance%20at%20a%20WWE%20event%2C%20January%202024%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d2062169253ccddf99147e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222125%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKai%20Cenat%20became%20famous%20as%20a%20livestreamer%20on%20Twitch%2C%20but%20you%20can%20now%20see%20him%20in%20all%20sorts%20of%20places%20%E2%80%94%20like%20this%20WWE%20%26quot%3BMonday%20Night%20Raw%26quot%3B%20broadcast%20from%20January.%3Cp%3EWWE%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20pandemic%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20discovered%20Twitch%2C%20and%20people%20spent%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20on%20Twitch.%20Then%20there%20was%20a%20rush%20from%20YouTube%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Facebook%20to%20build%20their%20own%20version%20of%20Twitch.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-did-ninja-make-for-leaving-twitch-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20offered%20huge%20contracts%20to%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20Twitch%20streamers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20Now%20they%20basically%20have%20all%20sort%20of%20retreated%20from%20that%20business.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20hope%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BI'll%20lose%20money%20on%20this%20creator.%20But%20all%20these%20users%20will%20come.%26quot%3B%20But%20when%20that%20creator%20left%20Twitch%2C%20there%20was%20another%20creator%20ready%20to%20step%20up%20and%20become%20the%20next%20big%20thing%20on%20Twitch.%20They%20filled%20that%20void.%20And%20so%20%5Brival%20platforms%5D%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20this%20doesn't%20work.%20We're%20not%20really%20pulling%20%5Baudience%5D%20from%20Twitch.%20So%20why%20do%20we%20want%20to%20keep%20losing%20money%20on%20these%20deals%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%20had%20deep-pocketed%20competitors%20that%20walked%20away.%20Does%20that%20mean%20they%20concluded%20they%20could%20never%20compete%3F%20Or%20did%20they%20decide%20this%20business%20is%20not%20worth%20it%20for%20them%20and%20they%20can%20get%20a%20better%20return%20doing%20something%20else%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20absolutely%20the%20case%20that%20the%20VOD%20business%2C%20like%20TikTok%20and%20YouTube%2C%20is%20a%20great%20business.%20You%20watch%20that%20when%20you%20have%20five%20minutes%20here%2C%20five%20minutes%20there%2C%20and%20you%20add%20up%20the%20five%20minutes%20%E2%80%A6%20it's%20a%20great%20business.%20I%20mean%2C%20it's%20bigger%20than%20our%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20thought%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20will%20be%20on%20top%20of%20our%20business.%26quot%3B%20And%20they%20still%20all%20do%20live.%20It's%20not%20like%20they%20pulled%20back%20from%20live.%20They've%20pulled%20back%20from%20signing%20money-losing%20deals.%20And%20when%20you%20pull%20back%20from%20that%20artificial%20injection%20of%20capital%2C%20Twitch%2C%20because%20it%20focuses%20on%20live%2C%20%5Bstreamers%20say%5D%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I'd%20rather%20be%20on%20Twitch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20while%20back%20Twitch%20was%20on%20the%20radar%20of%20media%20companies%2C%20and%20people%20like%20the%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F2017%2F9%2F13%2F16304278%2Fnba-twitch-adam-silver-tv-ratings-facebook-amazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENBA%20were%20saying%20they%20wanted%20their%20broadcasts%20to%20look%20more%20like%20Twitch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20They%20had%20demos%20where%20there%20was%20a%20basketball%20game%20going%20on%20with%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F2017%2F12%2F13%2F16769772%2Fnba-twitch-games-interactive-g-league-basketball-adam-silver%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eall%20Twitch%20stuff%20on%20the%20side%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20It%20doesn't%20look%20like%20that%20ever%20took%20off.%20Is%20that%20media%20companies%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BActually%2C%20we're%20not%20really%20ready%20for%20a%20Twitch-like%20experience%26quot%3B%3F%20Is%20that%20the%20audience%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20ready%20for%20that%26quot%3B%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it's%20people%20misunderstanding%20what%20is%20so%20special%20about%20Twitch.%20Let's%20take%20music.%20There's%20a%20ton%20of%20musicians%20on%20Twitch.%20And%20people%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20%E2%80%94%20we'll%20put%20music%20on%20Twitch.%20We're%20going%20to%20film%20a%20concert.%26quot%3B%20So%20you%20take%20one%20concert%20and%20you%20film%20it.%20But%20then%20the%20creator%20isn't%20interacting%20with%20the%20community%20online.%20It's%20not%20distinctly%20different%20than%20what%20you%20can%20watch%20in%20a%20VOD%2C%20right%3F%20And%20it%20happens%20once.%20So%20the%20people%20are%20not%20building%20community%20among%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20musicians%20that%20use%20Twitch%20%E2%80%94%20they%20often%20use%20Twitch%20more%20to%20engage%20with%20their%20audience%20and%20community%20and%20doing%20whatever%20they%20do%20in%20their%20free%20time.%20The%20poster%20child%20example%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitch.tv%2Ftpain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ET-Pain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who's%20a%20big%20musician%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkotaku.com%2Ftpain-y2k-rapper-twitch-nappy-boy-gaming-stream-team-1850067397%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20streams%20on%20Twitch%20all%20the%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'll%20chat%20with%20him%20and%20hang%20out%20with%20him%20on%20Twitch%2C%20and%20he%20games%20on%20Twitch.%20He%20does%20his%20sound%20recording%20on%20Twitch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20point%20is%2C%20it's%20not%20about%20taking%20traditional%20music%20media%20and%20sticking%20chat%20next%20to%20it.%20That%20doesn't%20create%20community.%20That%20is%20just%20traditional%20premium%20media%20with%20people%20chatting%20alongside%2C%20which%20they%20already%20do%20on%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20you%20became%20the%20Twitch%20CEO.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitch-ceo-layoffs-read-email-employees-dan-clancy-disappointed-amazon-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRead%2520the%2520email%2520Twitch%2527s%2520CEO%2Ca.m.%2520announcing%2520500%2520job%2520cuts%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520CEO%2520of%2520Twitch%2520emailed%2Creported%2520the%2520news%2520on%2520Tuesday.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThen%20you%20had%20layoffs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20Then%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F1%2F12%2F24035938%2Fill-be-blunt-were-not-profitable%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eyou%20said%20Twitch%20wasn't%20profitable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20which%20is%20why%20you%20made%20the%20cuts.%20It's%20kind%20of%20shocking%20to%20hear%20that%20between%20Amazon's%20resources%20and%20Twitch's%20cultural%20cachet%20that%20Twitch%20wasn't%20making%20money.%20Is%20it%20making%20money%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20don't%20talk%20about%20where%20we're%20at%20now.%20But%20when%20you%20say%20it's%20shocking%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20that%20shocking.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fearnings%2Fuber-q4-earnings-report-2023-4e0d59f6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%20didn't%20make%20money%20until%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYes%2C%20but%20they%20were%20in%20a%20different%20business.%20And%20YouTube%20was%20making%20money%20%E2%80%94%20not%20right%20away%2C%20but%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20at%20YouTube%20from%202010%20to%202012.%20For%20a%20long%20time%2C%20YouTube%20was%20not%20profitable.%20So%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20that%20strange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20is%20an%20issue%20in%20the%20tech%20space%2C%20where%20there%20is%20this%20mindset%20of%2C%20%26quot%3BBuild%20your%20organization%20for%20where%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20in%20three%20or%20four%20years.%26quot%3B%20That%20came%20out%20of%20Google%2C%20in%20part%20because%20Google%20was%20lucky%20enough%20to%20have%20a%20money%20machine%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20everyone%20else%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20like%20grow%2C%20grow%2C%20grow.%20Get%20a%20big%20team.%20Get%20a%20big%20team.%20And%20to%20be%20honest%2C%20part%20of%20what%20happened%20to%20Twitch%2C%20they%20kind%20of%20fell%20into%20that%20at%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Twitch%20team%2C%20when%20they%20first%20got%20there%2C%20they%20were%20very%20scrappy.%20And%20then%20people%20would%20come%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20no%2C%20no%2C%20that's%20not%20the%20game%20here.%20You%20have%20to%20argue%20for%20more%20resources.%26quot%3B%20And%20having%20been%20in%20Big%20Tech%2C%20that%20is%20the%20game%3A%20How%20do%20you%20argue%20for%20more%20resources%3F%20As%20opposed%20to%3A%20How%20do%20you%20figure%20out%20what%20is%20the%20number%20you%20need%20to%20serve%20your%20audience%20in%20your%20community%3F%20And%20so%20we%20were%20just%20like%20many%20other%20folks%20in%20tech.%20We%20were%20just%20not%20running%20the%20business%20as%20well%20as%20we%20could%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitch-ceo-dan-clancy-profitability-livestreaming-future-under-amazon-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741880855000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d2fd3d585f1dff88b209c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitch-ceo-dan-clancy-profitability-livestreaming-future-under-amazon-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Twitch%20practically%20invented%20livestreaming.%20Next%20challenge%3A%20keeping%20its%20audience%20and%20turning%20a%20profit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A43%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitch-ceo-dan-clancy-profitability-livestreaming-future-under-amazon-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wet%20vs.%20dry%20cat%20food%3A%20Which%20is%20better%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side-by-side%20image%20of%20a%20gray%20cat%20eating%20wet%20food%20off%20of%20a%20small%20plate%20and%20a%20gray%20and%20tan%20tabby%20cat%20eating%20dry%20food%20out%20of%20a%20green%20bowl.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d2ee03b8b41a9673fa886b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWet%20and%20dry%20cat%20foods%20each%20have%20unique%20benefits.%3Cp%3EWestend61%3B%20Larisa%20Stefanuyk%2FGetty%20Images%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBoth%20wet%20and%20dry%20cat%20food%20are%20nutritious%20options%20for%20cats.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDry%20food%20is%20easy%20to%20feed%20and%20costs%20less%2C%20while%20wet%20food%20is%20more%20hydrating%20and%20enticing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EVeterinarians%20say%20you%20can%20feed%20a%20healthy%20cat%20a%20combination%20of%20wet%20and%20dry%20food.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChoosing%20the%20right%20food%20for%20your%20cat%20means%20balancing%20its%20nutritional%20needs%20with%20your%20lifestyle%20and%20budget.%20Two%20of%20the%20most%20common%20cat%20food%20options%20are%20wet%20(canned)%20and%20dry%20(kibble)%2C%20and%20each%20has%20its%20own%20benefits.%20Dry%20cat%20food%20is%20a%20popular%20choice%20for%20its%20affordability%20and%20convenience%2C%20while%20wet%20food%20provides%20significantly%20more%20moisture%2C%20which%20some%20veterinarians%20recommend%20for%20specific%20health%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20dry%20versus%20wet%20cat%20food%2C%20including%20how%20each%20type%20is%20made%2C%20what%20sets%20them%20apart%2C%20and%20why%20you%20might%20opt%20for%20one%20over%20the%20other%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20a%20mix%20of%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201f592ca-e7ec-4314-9799-dc69a460d1b7%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22The%20differences%20between%20wet%20and%20dry%20cat%20food%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20differences%20between%20wet%20and%20dry%20cat%20food%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20canned%20foods%20and%20kibbles%20can%20meet%20your%20cat's%20nutritional%20needs%20%E2%80%94%20so%20long%20as%20the%20food%20is%20labeled%20complete%20and%20balanced%20for%20their%20life%20stage%20(kitten%2C%20adult%2C%20or%20all%20life%20stages)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aafco.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociation%20of%20American%20Feed%20Control%20Officials%20(AAFCO)%3C%2Fa%3E%20nutritional%20recommendations.%20The%20main%20differences%20between%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-wet-cat-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20wet%20cat%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dry-cat-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20dry%20cat%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20stem%20from%20how%20they're%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoisture%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECanned%20foods%20typically%20contain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fanimal-veterinary%2Fanimal-health-literacy%2Fcomplete-and-balanced-pet-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%25%20to%2078%25%20moisture%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%2010%25%20to%2012%25%20water%20in%20kibble.%20Dry%20food%20ingredients%20are%20mixed%2C%20cooked%2C%20and%20extruded%20(pushed%20through%20a%20small%20opening%20to%20form%20its%20shape)%2C%20then%20dried%20and%20coated%20with%20flavoring%20and%20preservatives.%20Wet%20cat%20food%20is%20mixed%20or%20blended%2C%20sealed%20into%20cans%2C%20and%20cooked%20inside%20the%20can%20using%20high-pressure%20steam%2C%20which%20is%20called%20retort%20cooking.%20Since%20the%20food%20is%20cooked%20inside%20the%20sealed%20can%2C%20water%20isn't%20lost%20during%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETexture%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dry%20food%20is%20crunchy%2C%20while%20wet%20food%20is%20moist%20and%20comes%20in%20a%20few%20textures%2C%20including%20shreds%2C%20smooth%20pates%2C%20or%20chunky%20bits.%20Cats%20can%20eat%20wet%2C%20dry%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20the%20two%20throughout%20their%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20even%20seniors%20without%20teeth%20may%20still%20enjoy%20crunchy%20kibbles.%20However%2C%20your%20cat%20may%20have%20a%20preference%20for%20one%20over%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECarbohydrates%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKibble%20generally%20has%20higher%20carbohydrate%20content%20than%20wet%20food%20because%20it%20requires%20starch%20to%20hold%20its%20shape%20%E2%80%94%20similar%20to%20how%20flour%20binds%20cookie%20dough%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mash.vet%2Fstaff%2Flisa-weeth-dvm-dacvn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Lisa%20Weeth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20board-certified%20veterinary%20nutritionist%20at%20Metropolitan%20Animal%20Specialty%20Hospital%20and%20founder%20of%20Weeth%20Nutrition%20Services.%20Carbohydrates%20are%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20a%20cat's%20diet%20that%20provides%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalories%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dry%20cat%20food%20is%20typically%20more%20calorie-dense%20than%20wet%20food.%20This%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20a%20cat%20on%20a%20dry%20food%20diet%20will%20gain%20excess%20weight%2C%20but%20it%20does%20mean%20they%20may%20need%20smaller%20portion%20sizes%20compared%20to%20wet%20food%20to%20meet%20their%20daily%20caloric%20needs.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20type%20of%20food%20you%20serve%2C%20veterinarians%20recommend%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-kitchen-scale%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekitchen%20scale%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20weigh%20portioned%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShelf%20life%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Unopened%20canned%20foods%20can%20last%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usda.gov%2Fabout-usda%2Fnews%2Fblog%2Fyou-toss-food-wait-check-it-out%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EU.S.%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Once%20opened%2C%20canned%20cat%20food%20should%20be%20refrigerated%20and%20used%20within%2048%20to%2072%20hours%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lsu.edu%2Fvetmed%2Ffaculty%2Fwelborn_nancy.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Nancy%20Welborn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20associate%20professor%20of%20community%20practice%20at%20Louisiana%20State%20University%20School%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%20If%20left%20out%20at%20room%20temperature%2C%20it%20should%20be%20used%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20an%20unopened%20bag%20of