t%20easy%20to%20buy%20in%20bulk%2C%20a%20convenient%2C%20cost-effective%20option%20whether%20you%20have%20one%20cat%20or%20multiple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalories%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Wet%20food%20may%20be%20ideal%20for%20cats%20who%20need%20to%20lose%20weight%2C%20as%20its%20high%20water%20content%20tends%20to%20fill%20a%20cat%20up%20while%20they're%20consuming%20fewer%20calories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fde6458-affa-46b2-992f-c4d1cd68b076%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Wet%20food%20cons%5C%22%3EWet%20food%20cons%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScent%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Because%20wet%20food%20has%20a%20strong%20odor%2C%20some%20caretakers%20may%20find%20serving%20and%20refrigerating%20it%20off-putting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECleanup%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Wet%20food%20creates%20more%20dishes%2C%20from%20serving%20utensils%20to%20washing%20bowls%20after%20every%20meal.%20And%20if%20you%20use%20a%20feeder%20puzzle%20to%20help%20slow%20your%20cat%20down%20while%20they%20eat%2C%20cleaning%20wet%20food%20from%20the%20cracks%20and%20crevices%20can%20be%20even%20more%20time-consuming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20and%20storage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Once%20open%2C%20wet%20cat%20food%20gradually%20loses%20its%20appeal%20and%20safety.%20Burns%20says%20to%20toss%20it%20after%20one%20to%20two%20hours%20at%20room%20temperature%2C%20or%20less%20when%20left%20out%20in%20warm%20environments%20or%20outdoors.%20Any%20unused%20food%20left%20in%20the%20can%20should%20be%20covered%20and%20refrigerated%20for%20no%20more%20than%2072%20hours.%20However%2C%20Welborn%20says%20some%20cats%20don't%20like%20cold%20food%2C%20so%20you%20may%20need%20to%20warm%20leftovers%20in%20the%20microwave%20before%20serving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAutomated%20feeding%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-feeder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20automatic%20cat%20feeders%3C%2Fa%3E%20offer%20portion%20control%2C%20scheduled%20feedings%2C%20and%20some%20even%20include%20a%20camera.%20However%2C%20the%20options%20for%20automatic%20wet%20food%20feeders%20are%20limited.%20Even%20the%20top%20performer%20in%20my%20testing%20could%20only%20keep%20meals%20at%20a%20safe%20temperature%20for%20about%2014%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Wet%20cat%20food%20tends%20to%20be%20pricier%20than%20kibble%2C%20but%20high-quality%20options%20across%20budgets%20exist.%20Hill's%2C%20Royal%20Canin%2C%20Purina%20Pro%20Plan%2C%20and%20Eukanuba%20offer%20a%20range%20of%20recipes%2C%20including%20some%20of%20the%20best%20budget-friendly%20cat%20foods%2C%20that%20are%20recommended%20by%20veterinarians.%20%26quot%3BThese%20brands%20have%20a%20board-certified%20veterinary%20nutritionist%20on%20staff%20ensuring%20the%20food%20is%20balanced%20and%20safe%20for%20consumption%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lovet.com%2Flocations%2Fil%2Fchicago%2F802-w-fulton-market%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Caitlin%20Johnson%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20at%20Lovet%20Pet%20Health%20Care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229457109a-510e-4af4-ad17-cc0b6f64a7f5%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Dry%20food%20pros%5C%22%3EDry%20food%20pros%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECleanup%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDry%20food%20is%20the%20easier%2C%20low-maintenance%20option%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20cleanup%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20no%20need%20for%20extra%20utensils%20like%20a%20spoon%20or%20fork.%20And%20rather%20than%20washing%20the%20bowl%20after%20every%20meal%2C%20one%20thorough%20wash%20each%20day%20is%20typically%20enough%20to%20keep%20the%20feeding%20station%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20and%20storage%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Kibble%20does%20not%20require%20refrigeration.%20Storing%20dry%20food%20in%20an%20airtight%20container%20helps%20keep%20it%20fresh%20for%20two%20to%20three%20months%20by%20protecting%20it%20from%20insects%2C%20rodents%2C%20and%20moisture.%20Plus%2C%20you%20can%20leave%20your%20cat's%20bowl%20out%20throughout%20the%20day%20without%20worrying%20about%20spoilage.%20This%20may%20reduce%20food%20waste%20if%20your%20cat%20prefers%20to%20graze%20on%20pre-portioned%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dry%20food%20usually%20costs%20less%20than%20wet%20food.%20It's%20also%20more%20calorie-dense%2C%20meaning%20smaller%20portions%20are%20needed%2C%20so%20one%20bag%20can%20provide%20many%20meals.%20Plus%2C%20dry%20food%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20go%20to%20waste%20since%20it%20doesn't%20spoil%20when%20left%20out%20for%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAutomatic%20feeders%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Automatic%20feeders%20can%20be%20really%20useful%2C%20especially%20for%20dry%20food%2C%20where%20overfeeding%20is%20a%20common%20concern.%20Plenty%20of%20feeders%20are%20made%20to%20dispense%20dry%20food%2C%20from%20budget-friendly%20feeders%20to%20those%20with%20a%20companion%20application%2C%20camera%2C%20or%20microchip-activated%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOral%20health%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESome%20dry%20cat%20foods%20can%20help%20remove%20plaque%20and%20tartar.%20These%20include%20both%20prescription%20and%20non-prescription%20recipes%20from%20Hill's%2C%20Purina%2C%20and%20Royal%20Canin.%20It's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20diets%20not%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvohc.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVeterinary%20Oral%20Health%20Council%20(VOHC)%3C%2Fa%3E%20list%20of%20accepted%20products%20have%20not%20been%20proven%20to%20improve%20oral%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4fde0b3-03be-40ed-8d44-56ad894ace9d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Dry%20food%20cons%5C%22%3EDry%20food%20cons%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShelf%20life%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20an%20unopened%20bag%20of%20dry%20cat%20food%20typically%20lasts%20several%20months%20to%20a%20few%20years%2C%20it%20has%20a%20shorter%20shelf%20life%20compared%20to%20unopened%20wet%20food.%20Plus%2C%20it's%20more%20susceptible%20to%20moisture%20and%20damage%20to%20the%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalories%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20it's%20not%20necessarily%20bad%20that%20dry%20food%20is%20generally%20more%20calorie-dense%20than%20wet%20food%2C%20it%20does%20mean%20that%20if%20portion%20control%20isn't%20strictly%20followed%2C%20cats%20may%20gain%20weight%20more%20quickly.%20However%2C%20because%20dry%20food%20can%20sit%20out%2C%20it's%20commonly%20used%20for%20free%20feeding%2C%20which%20Burns%20says%20isn't%20recommended.%20Free%20feeding%20can%20make%20it%20easy%20to%20lose%20track%20of%20how%20much%20cats%20are%20eating%2C%20especially%20when%20their%20bowls%20are%20continuously%20topped%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHydration%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDry%20food%20contains%20little%20moisture%2C%20so%20cats%20need%20to%20drink%20more%20water%20to%20stay%20hydrated.%20This%20doesn't%20always%20come%20naturally%20to%20cats.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20desert%20animals%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeth%20says.%20Some%20dry%20cat%20foods%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-foods-weight-loss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20weight%20loss%20foods%20for%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contain%20salt%20to%20encourage%20cats%20to%20drink.%20The%20moving%20water%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-fountain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecat%20water%20fountain%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20also%20help%20entice%20your%20cat%20to%20lap%20up%20more%20water%20throughout%20the%20day.%20%26quot%3BFor%20some%20medical%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20kidney%20disease%2C%20especially%20%E2%80%94%20an%20increase%20in%20water%20intake%20is%20recommended%20or%20preferred.%20Canned%20food%20is%20sometimes%20recommended%20to%20help%20with%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Welborn%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223362541b-ac9d-4ad5-a69f-9db838533664%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22When%20should%20I%20feed%20my%20cat%20dry%20or%20wet%20food%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20both%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20should%20I%20feed%20my%20cat%20dry%20or%20wet%20food%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20both%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20diet%20for%20your%20cat%2C%20the%20best%20guidance%20comes%20from%20your%20veterinarian.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20some%20situations%20where%20a%20dry%20food%20diet%20might%20be%20a%20better%20choice%20than%20wet%20and%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDry%20food%20can%20be%20a%20great%20option%20if%20your%20cat%20grazes%20throughout%20the%20day%20or%20simply%20prefers%20the%20taste%20and%20texture%20of%20kibble.%20It's%20also%20easier%20to%20serve%20and%20store%20once%20opened%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20practice%20portion%20control.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20your%20veterinarian%20may%20recommend%20a%20specific%20food%20that%20only%20comes%20in%20kibble%20form.%20If%20you're%20unable%20to%20brush%20your%20cat's%20teeth%20or%20want%20to%20add%20to%20their%20oral%20care%20routine%2C%20a%20dry%20cat%20food%20that's%20VOHC-accepted%20may%20be%20appropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWet%20cat%20food%20is%20a%20great%20option%20for%20pets%20that%20overeat%2C%20beg%20for%20food%2C%20or%20don't%20drink%20enough%20water.%20Its%20high%20moisture%20content%20supports%20hydration%20while%20promoting%20the%20feeling%20of%20fullness.%20Cats%20don't%20have%20a%20high%20thirst%20drive%2C%20says%20Burns.%20Therefore%2C%20vets%20often%20recommend%20wet%20food%20for%20conditions%20that%20benefit%20from%20extra%20hydration%2C%20such%20as%20kidney%20disease%2C%20urinary%20tract%20issues%2C%20and%20even%20hairballs.%20While%20canned%20food%20is%20easy%20to%20store%20before%20opening%2C%20serving%20it%20can%20be%20less%20convenient%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20still%20can't%20choose%20between%20the%20two%2C%20you%20might%20not%20have%20to.%20Our%20sources%20say%20offering%20kittens%20a%20variety%20of%20wet%20and%20dry%20food%20textures%2C%20flavors%2C%20and%20even%20different%20shapes%20of%20dry%20food%20helps%20promote%20food%20flexibility.%20If%20your%20cat's%20favorite%20food%20is%20unavailable%2C%20the%20recipe%20changes%2C%20or%20they%20need%20a%20diet%20change%20for%20medical%20reasons%2C%20this%20can%20make%20the%20transition%20much%20smoother%20or%20even%20possible.%20Cats%20in%20middle%20age%20or%20older%20often%20won't%20eat%20new%20food%20types%20or%20textures%20because%20they%20don't%20recognize%20it%20as%20food%2C%20Weeth%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dcc9e856-d2f2-476b-8fa9-e1cb368cbd08%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22The%20bottom%20line%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bottom%20line%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWet%20food%20is%20more%20appealing%20to%20cats%20because%20it's%20moist%20and%20has%20a%20strong%20aroma.%20However%2C%20kibble%20provides%20the%20same%20nutritional%20value%20and%20is%20often%20cheaper%20and%20more%20convenient%20for%20people.%20That%20said%2C%20dry%20food%20is%20more%20calorie-dense%20and%20easier%20to%20overfeed%2C%20making%20portion%20control%20even%20more%20important.%20Unless%20your%20cat%20has%20a%20strong%20preference%20or%20your%20vet%20recommends%20a%20specific%20diet%20for%20a%20health%20condition%2C%20there's%20no%20need%20to%20choose%20just%20one.%20In%20fact%2C%20exposing%20kittens%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20textures%2C%20flavors%2C%20and%20food%20shapes%20can%20help%20prevent%20picky%20eating%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fwet-vs-dry-cat-food%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741880789000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d2ee10585f1dff88b2064e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets